Files : &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;debian/rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="11002" author="brian" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 13:09:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patrick, I&apos;ve added you to this bug to reply to your gerrit comment:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From the debian pov this patch is okay, however I would prefer another distribution- independent solution for this scenario.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given that this entire solution is about running autogen.sh in debian/rules files when it&apos;s determined to be necessary, I&apos;m not sure I understand what you mean about a distribution-independent solution.  Can you expand?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
